the Simplify to Grow Program, lower manufacturing costs, lower intangible asset impairment charges, lower advertising
and consumer promotion costs and favorable volume/mix. These favorable items were partially offset by higher raw
material costs, the impact of divestitures, unfavorable currency and higher other selling, general and administrative
expenses (net of prior-year property insurance recovery).
