Table of Contents
In 2020, we estimate that our pension contributions will be $16 million to our U.S. plans and $230 million to our non-
U.S. plans based on current tax laws. Our actual contributions may be different due to many factors, including changes
in tax and other benefit laws, significant differences between expected and actual pension asset performance or
interest rates.
